The paper deals with distributed clustering algorithms, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The focus on beyond worst-case analysis and approximation stability suggests a connection to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The use of $k$-median and $k$-means clustering problems suggests a connection to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
